        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 4:55PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Midas, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of western Elko
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
